{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe live Jira/LLM external tier (`tests/external/`) runs only on `workflow_dispatch`\n(`.github/workflows/external-integration.yml`), which sets `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL=1` and maps\n`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`/`OPENAI_API_KEY` but **no `JIRA_*` secrets** and does **not install the\n`acli` binary** — and `test_link_sync_roundtrip_live.py::_live_jira_ready()` gates on BOTH\n(`creds and shutil.which(\"acli\")`). So the live Jira round-trip can only ever SKIP: Jira\nAPI/SDK drift merges through normal CI with no real integration signal, and nothing fails a\nrun in which the whole external tier silently skips. VALIDATED.\n\nCorrection to the earlier framing: the live test is NOT read-only — it calls `create_issue`\ntwice + `set_relationship`, then in a `try/finally` deletes every artifact it created (links\nthen issues). It makes REAL, self-cleaning Jira mutations against whatever project the creds\npoint at, so it requires a DEDICATED disposable test project, not a shared one.\n\n## What\n1. **Workflow** (`external-integration.yml`): add an `on.schedule` cron trigger (weekly)\n   alongside `workflow_dispatch`; map `JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER`/`JIRA_API_TOKEN` from `secrets.*`\n   into the external job's env; and INSTALL the `acli` binary by reusing the established\n   download+verify+install step from `reconcile-bridge.yml` (pinned `vars.ACLI_VERSION` +\n   `vars.ACLI_SHA256`, sha256-checked), adding `~/.acli` to `PATH` so `shutil.which(\"acli\")`\n   resolves. Without this step the Jira tests skip even when secrets are set.\n2. **Fail-on-all-skip canary** (`tests/external/conftest.py`): add a pytest session hook that,\n   when `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is truthy (a real scheduled/dispatch run), REPORTS the\n   external-tier executed-vs-skipped counts and FAILS the session if EVERY external test\n   skipped (zero executed) — turning a creds-/acli-less all-skip run RED instead of a false\n   green, so drift is surfaced. When `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is unset (the default suite, where\n   the tier is intentionally inert), the hook is a no-op.\n3. **Tests**:\n   - a behavioral test of the fail-on-all-skip hook: an all-skipped external session with\n     `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL=1` makes the hook signal failure; ≥1 executed passes; unset\n     `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is a no-op.\n   - a config-as-artifact test asserting `external-integration.yml` declares an `on.schedule`\n     trigger, maps `JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER`/`JIRA_API_TOKEN` into the external job env, AND\n     installs `acli` / puts it on PATH (a drift guard mirroring the repo's YAML-artifact tests).\n\n## Scope\n- `.github/workflows/external-integration.yml` — schedule + JIRA_* env + acli install/PATH.\n- `tests/external/conftest.py` — fail-on-all-skip session hook + executed/skipped report.\n- A test module (e.g. `tests/unit/test_external_canary.py`) — the hook behavior + workflow wiring.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The workflow declares an `on.schedule` trigger, maps `JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER`/\n      `JIRA_API_TOKEN` into the external job env, and installs the `acli` binary onto PATH; a\n      config-as-artifact test pins all three.\n- [ ] The conftest FAILS an external session in which every external test skipped (with\n      `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL=1`) and is a no-op when `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is unset — asserted by a\n      behavioral test of the hook.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] The `JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER`/`JIRA_API_TOKEN` secrets AND the\n      `ACLI_VERSION`/`ACLI_SHA256` repo variables are configured in the GitHub repo, and a\n      DEDICATED disposable Jira test project is provisioned for the self-cleaning live\n      mutations — these require GitHub repo-admin + a Jira project and cannot be done from the\n      code change; attested by the operator with the config evidence.\n- [ ] `make lint && make test` green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783809536325765001,"uuid":"c021cc61-4b15-4ec2-83c9-3223c18aedf8"}